  "details": "memcached is a high-performance, distributed memory object caching system, generic in nature, but intended for use in speeding up dynamic web applications by alleviating database load.   \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * memcached: memcached: Username enumeration via timing side channel (CVE-2026-47783)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
